behaviours.label: Daily deep-work block on highest-leverage client project
behaviours.notes: Protects a 90–120 minute block for focused work on the single most leveraged client deliverable, with notifications off and a clear objective.

behaviours.label: Weekly strategic review and roadmap for all clients
behaviours.notes: Reviews open engagements, risks, and opportunities; updates a single page per client with next moves, scope, and expected impact.

behaviours.label: Proactive stakeholder 1:1s with client sponsors
behaviours.notes: Holds recurring 1:1s with economic buyers and key stakeholders to clarify objectives, manage expectations, and surface hidden constraints.

behaviours.label: Curated reading of AI research and industry reports
behaviours.notes: Maintains a short, high-signal reading queue of research papers, newsletters, and market analyses, captured with brief summaries.

behaviours.label: Publishing long-form thought pieces or internal memos
behaviours.notes: Writes structured essays or memos on AI strategy, risks, and implementation patterns to clarify thinking and demonstrate expertise.

behaviours.label: Speaking at conferences, podcasts, or panels
behaviours.notes: Accepts a small number of high-leverage speaking opportunities that reach ideal clients and peers, with careful preparation.

behaviours.label: Blocking no-meeting deep-work mornings three times per week
behaviours.notes: Protects specific mornings in the calendar from meetings to ensure uninterrupted time for design, modeling, and writing.

behaviours.label: End-of-day shutdown ritual and tomorrow planning
behaviours.notes: Closes loops by capturing open tasks, choosing three priorities for tomorrow, and reviewing the calendar to avoid surprises.

behaviours.label: Late-night email triage in bed
behaviours.notes: Checks and responds to work email in bed before sleep, often reopening loops and reactivating work-related worries.

behaviours.label: Weekly 1:1s with direct reports
behaviours.notes: Runs structured 1:1s with reports to remove blockers, clarify priorities, and support their development.

behaviours.label: Delegating and documenting repeatable processes
behaviours.notes: Turns ad-hoc tasks into documented checklists or SOPs and hands them off where possible.

behaviours.label: Daily 45-minute strength and mobility training
behaviours.notes: Combines strength, mobility, and light cardio to build resilience and reduce pain from long hours at a desk.

behaviours.label: Evening family dinner without devices
behaviours.notes: Sits down for shared dinner with partner and kids, with phones and laptops out of sight.

behaviours.label: Weekend planning session with partner
behaviours.notes: Reviews the upcoming week’s logistics, commitments, and childcare with partner, aligning expectations and adjusting load.

behaviours.label: Batch-processing household admin and bills
behaviours.notes: Groups recurring admin like bills, paperwork, and renewals into one focused block instead of scattering them through the week.

behaviours.label: Maintaining shared calendar and chore board
behaviours.notes: Keeps a shared digital calendar and a visible chore board up to date to reduce coordination overhead.

behaviours.label: Daily 15-minute mindfulness or breathwork
behaviours.notes: Practices a short, simple meditation or breathwork protocol to down-regulate and notice cognitive/emotional load.

behaviours.label: Weekly therapy or coaching session
behaviours.notes: Works with a therapist/coach to process stress, challenge blind spots, and refine narratives about work and family.

behaviours.label: Strict sleep window and wind-down routine
behaviours.notes: Keeps a consistent sleep schedule with a 60-minute wind-down that excludes work and bright screens.

behaviours.label: Saying yes to every interesting work opportunity
behaviours.notes: Reflexively accepts new projects, collaborations, and advisory roles without first rebalancing commitments.

behaviours.label: Weekly long-form journaling and self-review
behaviours.notes: Writes several pages reflecting on wins, failures, emotions, and strategic direction across work, family, and health.

behaviours.label: Playing piano or guitar improvisation
behaviours.notes: Spends unstructured time improvising on an instrument, focusing on texture, mood, and play rather than performance.

behaviours.label: Reading literary fiction or essays before bed
behaviours.notes: Reads non-work writing that is aesthetically rich and reflective, as a bridge between the day and sleep.

behaviours.label: Weekend hikes or long walks in nature
behaviours.notes: Spends several hours outdoors walking or hiking, ideally with family or a close friend.

behaviours.label: Hosting small dinner salons with friends
behaviours.notes: Invites a small group for dinner and structured conversation about ideas, books, and current problems.

behaviours.label: Tinkering with personal coding or maker projects
behaviours.notes: Builds small tools, prototypes, or physical projects for curiosity rather than work ROI.

behaviours.label: Quarterly solo retreat day without devices
behaviours.notes: Takes a day alone offline with notebook and books to review life direction and reset priorities.

behaviours.label: Learning non-work topics like art, history, or philosophy
behaviours.notes: Regularly studies subjects unrelated to AI or consulting to broaden perspective and feed creativity.

behaviours.label: Traveling with family to new places
behaviours.notes: Plans and takes trips together to explore new environments, food, and cultures.

behaviours.label: Impulsive social media scrolling between tasks
behaviours.notes: Frequently opens social apps between tasks for stimulation, fragmenting attention and eroding focus.

outcomes.label: Trusted strategic advisor to C-suite clients
outcomes.notes: Clients see them as a long-term partner on AI strategy rather than a tactical vendor, leading to influence over key decisions.

outcomes.label: Pipeline of high-value AI consulting engagements
outcomes.notes: A steady flow of well-scoped, well-paid projects with clients that are good strategic fits.

outcomes.label: Strong executive team relationships
outcomes.notes: Deep trust and open communication with internal and client executives, enabling honest conversations about risks and trade-offs.

outcomes.label: Calm, predictable household routines
outcomes.notes: Mornings, evenings, and weekends run with low friction; everyone understands the basic rhythm and expectations.

outcomes.label: High baseline physical energy
outcomes.notes: Most days feel physically energetic rather than sluggish, with fewer crashes and aches.

outcomes.label: Resilient nervous system and stress tolerance
outcomes.notes: Stressful events are handled without frequent overwhelm or reactivity, with quick return to baseline.

outcomes.label: Clear prioritisation across work and life domains
outcomes.notes: At any given time, they know what matters most and what can safely be ignored or deferred.

outcomes.label: Deep industry and technical credibility
outcomes.notes: Peers and clients recognize them as a thoughtful, well-informed voice on AI technology and its business implications.

outcomes.label: Well-run home finances and admin
outcomes.notes: Bills are paid, paperwork is up-to-date, and financial surprises are rare.

outcomes.label: Rich, playful time with partner and kids
outcomes.notes: Regular pockets of connection that feel present, light, and fun rather than rushed or distracted.

outcomes.label: Diverse, stimulating social circle
outcomes.notes: A mix of friends and peers from different domains who challenge and inspire new thinking.

outcomes.label: Regular immersion in flow states
outcomes.notes: Frequent periods of deep absorption in work or hobbies, with a sense of effortlessness and satisfaction.

outcomes.label: Creative portfolio outside of work
outcomes.notes: A small but growing body of creative work—music, writing, or projects—that is not tied to career outcomes.

outcomes.label: Continual learning across disciplines
outcomes.notes: A steady accumulation of understanding in areas beyond AI, such as art, history, and philosophy.

outcomes.label: Opportunities for mentorship and teaching
outcomes.notes: Regular chances to advise, teach, or mentor others in a way that feels meaningful and energising.

outcomes.label: Periodic travel and micro-adventures
outcomes.notes: Life includes trips and small adventures that disrupt routine and create vivid memories.

outcomes.label: Low-clutter, functional home environment
outcomes.notes: Spaces are easy to use, not overloaded with stuff, and support the activities that actually matter.

outcomes.label: Good sleep quality and recovery
outcomes.notes: Sleep feels restorative, with relatively few nights of insomnia or restless waking.

outcomes.label: Time buffers and slack in weekly schedule
outcomes.notes: The calendar has deliberate white space that can absorb overruns and surprises without constant rushing.

outcomes.label: Fragmented attention and shallow work
outcomes.notes: Work blocks are riddled with context switching and low-impact tasks, making progress feel unsatisfying.

values.label: Impactful contribution to the AI ecosystem
values.notes: Wants their work to meaningfully shape how organisations use AI in a safe, thoughtful, and effective way.

values.label: Financial security and optionality
values.notes: Values having enough wealth and stability to choose projects and pace without fear-driven decisions.

values.label: Deep family connection and presence
values.notes: Cares about being emotionally available and actively involved in partner and children’s lives.

values.label: Physical health and longevity
values.notes: Wants a strong, resilient body that supports decades of active life and work.

values.label: Mental clarity and emotional balance
values.notes: Prioritises clear thinking, emotional regulation, and a feeling of inner steadiness.

values.label: Autonomy and freedom over time
values.notes: Wants high control over what they work on, when, and with whom.

values.label: Mastery and intellectual growth
values.notes: Feels alive when learning, synthesising, and pushing the edge of their competence.

values.label: Joy, play, and aesthetic pleasure
values.notes: Wants life to include beauty, playfulness, and experiences that are good for their own sake.

values.label: Contribution to community and mentees
values.notes: Wants to help others grow, especially younger practitioners and peers in the AI space.

values.label: Integrity and ethical impact
values.notes: Wants alignment between values and behaviour, especially around the societal implications of AI.

values.label: Adventure and exploration
values.notes: Values novelty, exploration, and experiences that stretch comfort zones.

values.label: Spiritual reflection and meaning
values.notes: Wants time to reflect on larger questions of meaning, purpose, and orientation to life.

values.label: Orderly, low-friction daily life
values.notes: Prefers systems and environments that reduce unnecessary friction and decision fatigue.

values.label: Creative self-expression
values.notes: Cares about expressing their inner world through music, writing, or other media, even if it’s not public.
